
OS: GNU/Linux: xubuntu flavor of Ubuntu 14.04
This is not portable code.


We use a custom installation of OpenSceneGraph (OSG) tagged as:
  TAG=OpenSceneGraph-3.5.1
which we got from running:
  git clone git://github.com/openscenegraph/osg.git
and dumping the tagged version with something like:
  git archive  --format=tar $TAG | $(cd "$builddir" && tar -xf -)
and lots of pain building the installing OSG.


We started by following the examples in the book:
http://ahux.narod.ru/olderfiles/1/OpenSceneGraph.3.0.Beginners.Guide-3208.pdf





and
http://ahux.narod.ru/olderfiles/1/OSG3_Cookbook.pdf


Each of the examples in different directories [0-9][0-9]_*/ do not
depend on other examples, but depend on some files in common/

